Alexandra residents are targeting shops owned by foreign nationals. eNCA's Lindokuhle Xulu has more. #eNCA Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Some Alexandra residents are planning a total shutdown in protest over undocumented foreign nationals in the area. A group calling themselves the Alex Dudula Movement, which is not linked to Operation Dudula, is responsible. READ: Operation Dudula targets undocumented hawkers in Hillbrow Alex residents say the shutdown will continue until their demands for foreign nationals to leave are met. Residents allege foreigners are responsible for rising crime levels, drug dealing and stealing jobs from South African citizens. Watch the video above for more details on this story. Reporter Lindokuhle Xulu has more #eNCA Courtesy #DStv403 Reporter Lindokuhle Xulu has more #eNCA Courtesy #DStv403